div.div: When the disaster called "Portal Impact" ended it left Park Hyun-So to pick up the pieces after his parents' death and his younger brother was left in a deep coma. Years later after suffering hardships and massively in debt due to his brother's hospital bills, Hyun-Soo meets Chung-Yeong, a martial artist from another world! Chung-Yeong, a murim martial master who had been astral projecting could not return to his body, when a portal appeared and sucked him in, taking him to modern Korea. After months not being able to interact with anyone Chung-Yeong out of boredom takes on Hyun-Soo as his student and begins to teach him martial arts
Gate: Jieitai Kanochi nite, Kaku Tatakaeri

One day in the 21st century, a gate opened in the middle of the Ginza district of Tokyo. Out of the gate poured soldiers and strange creatures, and they soon made Ginza look like an image of hell. The gate apparently connected Japan to another world, a world with a militant empire and many supernatural creatures. The Japanese Self-Defense Force decided to send a small group, led by a soldier who's also an otaku, into the other world on a reconnaissance mission. They're meant to learn what they can about the empire (and its plans), the world, and the people. They're hardly in the world yet, though, when they come across a village destroyed by a giant fire-breathing dragon. The only survivor is an unconscious elven girl they find hidden in a well. Now they feel like they must warn the nearby towns about the dragon, and do what they can to help. On the way, they'll meet more magical, female companions, and learn more about this dangerous new world.
